<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-14 10:57 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7507 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SALMA-HAYEK15-COX     04-14 0426
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SALMA-HAYEK15-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Hayek a prankster with perfect almond eyes
 &HT;    By Loretta Grantham
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Just five to 10 minutes, they said, and
no photos.
</P>
<P>
   (ITAL)No photos?!(END ITAL)
</P>
<P>
   ``She hasn't been made up,'' an assistant apologizes. ``You
understand.''
</P>
<P>
   (ITAL) No, I do not. She'd look better after a greased pig chase
than I would after a day at Georgette Klinger. (END ITAL)
</P>
<P>
   Salma Hayek, the bewitching Mexican bombshell who has boys doing
backflips, was in town recently for the Palm Beach International
Film Festival. She came for a screening of her new flick The
Velocity of Gary, but is best known for steaming, er, starring with
Antonio Banderas in 1995's Desperado. She's also a Revlon model.
</P>
<P>
   And also a tad somber. Today, anyway. Legs tucked under her,
she's perched on a couch receiving reporters one at a time.
Although a childhood prankster, Hayek, 30, isn't one to make mirth,
as if being all business will make folks take her more seriously.
(Either that, or she's never been asked which Pop-Tart is her
favorite. It's strawberry).
</P>
<P>
   With wristwatch ticking and a personal goal of seven minutes
flat, I quiz on ...
</P>
<P>
   Funniest English screwup? Transposing letters. ``I say O.B.
instead of B.O. when I mean somebody smells bad.''
</P>
<P>
   Laundry detergent? ``I have no idea, but I have a very good
maid.''
</P>
<P>
   Worst thing you did to your kid brother? ``I shaved his head
when he was about eight.''
</P>
<P>
   Colored contact lenses? ``Never in my life!'' (She has
almond-shaped brown eyes. Starlets always have almond-shaped eyes.)
</P>
<P>
   Gas or electric stove? ``Gas.''
</P>
<P>
   Figure flaw? ``I have one, but I am not talking about it.''
</P>
<P>
   Best prank in Catholic school: ``I set all the nuns' clocks back
three hours.'' (She was expelled, but not just for that.)
</P>
<P>
   Repair ripped pantyhose with nail polish or just toss 'em? ``I
throw them away. Unless they are my last pair.''
</P>
<P>
   Banderas' best body part? ``His eyes. No, wait. His hands.''
</P>
<P>
   Favorite fast-food item? ``I do not eat fast food. I eat heavy
food. Like pork.''
</P>
<P>
   Use little hotel soap or bring your own? ``I use the hotel's. I
would not stay in a place with bad soap.''
</P>
<P>
   Favorite candle scent? ``Tuberose.''
</P>
<P>
   Number of failed engagements? Four.
</P>
<P>
   What gives? ``I will get married when I meet a man who has more
(chutzpah) than I do.''
</P>
<P>
   Loretta Grantham writes for the Palm Beach Post, West Palm
Beach, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
