officials are spending billions on new campaigns, even buying
expensive ads on prime time TV. It's called social marketing _ part
behavioral science, part propaganda, part Madison Avenue _ and it
has become the most popular political antidote to society's many
shortfalls. By ROBERT SALLADAY.
