   FBN-DRAFT-FARRIS (Undated) _ Kris Farris opted to pass up his
senior season with the the Bruins for the NFL for nothing other
than what a former Giant general manager labeled the ``planet
theroy of football.'' By Mark Blaudschun. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-COLUMN (Undated) _ League officials should seriously
consider either abolishing the shootout or relegating it to a lower
division. By Frank Dell'Apa.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-KRONE (Undated) _ Julie Krone, 35, the winningest female
jockey, had left a lasting impression on her sport before she
announced her retirement last week. By Joe Sullivan. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-HARRICK (Kingston, R.I.) _ Each working day Jim Harrick Jr.
enters the coaches' office at URI, he takes his position between a
rock and a hard place. By Joe Burris. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
