<SLUG> BC-GOODYKOONTZ-COLUMN-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DADDY DUTY CAN BE A DIRTY JOB 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BILL GOODYKOONTZ  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - How many parents have hunkered down with their
children in an attempt to do something constructive _ feed them,
read them a story, frantically try to persuade them to stop
screaming until they throw up _ and failed in the effort?
</P>
<P>
   Or, more to the point, how many haven't? Any?
</P>
<P>
   And it's not just coincidence. The little devils seem to have
their own agendas. You can tell by the looks on their faces that
they're up to something.
</P>
<P>
   If only we could tell what they were thinking. . . .
</P>
<P>
   Parent, smiling maniacally: OK! It's time for lunch! Let's just
put this bib on so we don't get too messy.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Oh great. Just choke me, why don't you? And what's this?
``Daddy's little girl'' _ gee, that's original. And you wonder why
I spit up on it.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Let's see, what looks good today? Creamed spinach?
Creamed corn? Beef and vegetable medley?
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Anything but prunes. Explosive results. You don't want to
have to do laundry again.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Let's go with these leftover creamed beets. . . . Wait a
second, sweetheart. Sit up straight in the high chair. Where do you
think you're going?
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Are you kidding? Have you ever eaten creamed beets? They
tasted like dirty bath water when they were fresh. Leftovers? I'm
outta here.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: All right, that's a good girl. You're strapped in now.
Isn't that better?
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Belt . . . too . . . tight. Stomach . .. squished. Feeling
. . . faint.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: You're certainly holding still now. OK, let's try a
bite.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Well, maybe just one.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Good girl! Hmm. Now that's a funny face.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Arggh! This is worse than the dog treat I found under the
couch!
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Let's try another one. Aw, now come on, honey. This is
good for you.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: That's what you said about immunizations, pal. I may have
been born at night, but it wasn't last night.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Choo-choo-choo. Here comes the train. Open up the
tunnel. Whoo-hoo!
</P>
<P>
   Baby: How embarrassing for you.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Come on, baby. Just a bite. Look, it's an airplane!
Bzzzzzzzzz.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Ha. I wish we had this on film.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Shoot. Come on, baby, just try a little bit more.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Poor guy. He's working so hard. But I'd rather grow
another tooth than eat this rot. Wait, I have an idea. That's
right, bring that spoon a little closer. . . .
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Good girl! Now open . . . Hey! Let go of the spoon!
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Ha, ha. This always gets them.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Keep your hands out of it. It's sticky!
</P>
<P>
   Baby: And now, for the grand finale.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: No! Keep it out of your hair!
</P>
<P>
   Baby: You'd think they would learn faster.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: OK, if that's how you're going to behave, it's not going
to be fun anymore.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: I love a challenge.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: If I'm going to have to pry your mouth open, so be it.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: What? What's he doing?
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Let's just get a little of this in there, and . . .
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Ugggle. Some of it got in my mouth! I hate to do this, but
desperate times call for desperate measures.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: OW!! Don't bite me! Man, those teeth are sharp.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Sorry.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: All right, fun's over. I'll just use the spoon to pry
your mouth open. Bite away!
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Ack. This isn't working.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: There you go. Now it's going down.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: No! (shudder) Yuck! Think!
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Isn't this yummy?
</P>
<P>
   Baby: I've got it!
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Good gi. . . what are you doing?
</P>
<P>
   Baby: This never fails.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Eww. What's that smell?
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Heh-heh.
</P>
<P>
   Parent: Aw, baby. Now I've got to change your diaper. Sigh. OK,
let's go.
</P>
<P>
   Baby: Hey, it beats creamed beets. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Reach Bill Goodykoontz at bill.goodykoontz(at)pni.com via e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
