<P>
   IRS-PUBLIC (Washington) _ The Internal Revenue Service is
remaking itself, pushing aside a culture that regarded all
taxpayers as being one audit away from punishment and, instead,
adopting a goal of helping people comply with the tax laws. Its
unfathomable audit notices are being rewritten in plain English.
And employees whose job is to answer questions from taxpayers will
soon have easy access to a basic tool that until recently few had:
a copy of the Internal Revenue Code. By David Cay Johnston.
</P>
