<P>
   SCI-GENOME-MAP (Undated) _ Ten pharmaceutical companies and the
Wellcome Trust of London are pooling efforts to create a fine-scale
map of the human genome. Their goal is to speed the discovery of
the genetic variations that underlie disease, and hence of new
drugs. The plan is designed to complement the human genome project,
an effort to decode the 3 billion letter genetic message that
resides in every human cell. By Nicholas Wade. (1200 words)
