<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMFORTCUISINE-2ndTake-TEX </SLUG>
 
UNDATED: in the Kitchen'' 
<TEXT>
<P>
   GOLDEN MASHED POTATOES WITH MORELS AND BAKED EGGS
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup dried morels (1/2 ounce)
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup boiling water
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 pounds Yukon gold potatoes, peeled and cut into 2-inch
chunks
</P>
<P>
   6 garlic cloves, peeled
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil
</P>
<P>
   1 large onion, coarsely chopped
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup heavy cream, divided
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly ground pepper
</P>
<P>
   4 large eggs
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup freshly grated Asiago or Parmesan cheese
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon minced chives
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In heatproof bowl, cover morels
with boiling water and let stand for about 15 minutes to soften.
Drain, reserving water, rinse and coarsely chop.
</P>
<P>
   In a large saucepan, cover potatoes and garlic with water and
boil over high heat until fork-tender. Drain and return to pan. Dry
over moderately high heat, shaking the pan, for about 1 minute.
Work through a ricer or mash by hand in a large bowl.
</P>
<P>
   In a large skillet, heat the oil. Add the onion; cook over low
heat, stirring often, until soft and golden. Add the morels and 1/4
cup of the cream and simmer for 2 minutes. Add onion mixture to
potatoes with the remaining 1/2 cup of heavy cream and the reserved
mushroom water; season with salt and pepper.
</P>
<P>
   Spoon the potatoes into a buttered, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking
dish. Make 4 shallow indentations in the potatoes and break an egg
into each. Sprinkle the cheese over all. Bake for about 12 minutes,
or until the egg whites are set and yolks are softly cooked.
Garnish with the chives and serve at once.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 571 calories, 41 grams fat, 34
grams carbohydrates, 18 grams protein, 388 milligrams cholesterol,
306 milligrams sodium, 65 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``1999 Food &AMP; Wine annual'' ($29.95, American Express
Publishing)
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   GRILLED DEVILED HAM AND CHEESE
</P>
<P>
   Makes 2 sandwiches
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons Dijon mustard
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce
</P>
<P>
   Dash cayenne pepper, optional
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup chopped ham
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup chopped or shredded Cheddar cheese
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon chopped pickle, French cornichon preferred
</P>
<P>
   2 slices sourdough bread, cut about 1/2-inch thick
</P>
<P>
   In a small bowl, combine the mustard, Worcestershire and
optional cayenne. Add the ham, cheese and pickle and stir until
well-combined.
</P>
<P>
   Spread this mixture over one side of each slice of bread. Broil
in an oven or toaster oven until cheese has melted and begins to
turn brown.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per sandwich: 268 calories, 14 grams fat,
23 grams carbohydrates, 12 grams protein, 33 milligrams
cholesterol, 753 milligrams sodium, 48 percent of calories from
fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Chicago Tribune
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   GRILLED FRESH GOAT CHEESE AND BACON SANDWICH
</P>
<P>
   Makes 2
</P>
<P>
   1 individual French bread roll
</P>
<P>
   Olive oil
</P>
<P>
   6 tablespoons fresh goat cheese, at room temperature
</P>
<P>
   2 strips bacon, cooked and crumbled
</P>
<P>
   4 teaspoons medium-hot salsa
</P>
<P>
   Cut the roll in half horizontally. Sprinkle olive oil over each
cut half. In a small bowl, combine goat cheese and bacon. Spread
this mixture over each cut half. Spoon salsa over the cheese.
</P>
<P>
   Broil in an oven or toaster oven until cheese is hot and begins
to brown.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis, per sandwich: 238 calories, 15 grams fat,
17 grams carbohydrates, 9 grams protein, 23 milligrams cholesterol,
398 milligrams sodium, 56 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Chicago Tribune
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
