<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Washington) _ Serbian forces shell an Albanian
village as NATO capitalizes on clear weather to step up air raids
inside Yugoslavia. Meanwhile, European leaders consider a German
peace proposal that calls for a 24-hour halt to the bombing if the
Serbs begin pulling troops out of Kosovo. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-KOSOVO (Washington) _ Congress receives a first-hand
account of the Kosovo refugee crisis as three ethnic Albanians move
lawmakers to tears with their stories of being forced at gunpoint
to leave their homeland. They urge Congress to help them and other
refugees return to Kosovo in peace. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
