   TAX-CUT (Washington) _ While lawmakers have trumpeting tax cuts
for months, the nation's key tax experts say there won't be room in
the budget for any kind of sizable tax reduction for at least a few
years. ``It is exceedingly unlikely _ almost impossible _ that we
would have a tax cut to affect 1999,'' said Rep. Bill Archer,
R-Texas, chairman of the House Ways and Means Committee. By DAVID
IVANOVICH.
</P>
