<P>
   CALIFORNIA-EAST-BAY-KOSOVO Reaction from the East Bay's
congressional delegation and California's senators to the war in
Kosovo. Despite a national reputation for dovishness, Bay Area
members appear to be just as torn about what to do in the Balkans
as the rest of the country. (650 words.) By Mark Stricherz
</P>
<P>
   IDAHO-PAGE. Rep. Mike Simpson nominated Ashley Stevens, a Twin
Falls native, for a summer House page position. (Brief.) By Robin
Brown
</P>
<P>
   MASSACHUSETTS-FEDERAL-DOLLARS. The federal government returned
$37 billion last year to Massachusetts in the form of Social
Security checks, defense contracts and grant awards that fund
programs and projects ranging from Medicaid to highway
construction, according to the Census Bureau. (550 words.) By Mark
D. Preston
</P>
<P>
   MICHIGAN-KOSOVO-TESTIMONY. The humanitarian crisis unfolding in
the Balkans was brought into a congressional hearing room Wednesday
as three Albanians who fled their homes in Kosovo told a Senate
subcommittee a series of harrowing stories about the organized
campaign of ethnic cleansing being waged by the forces of Yugoslav
President Slobodan Milosevic. (700 words.) By C.J. Karamargin
</P>
<P>
   NEW MEXICO-CAMPAIGN-UDALL. Rep. Tom Udall and fellow lawmakers
Wednesday signed a petition urging Congress to reform the country's
PENNSYLVANIA-SHIP. Philadelphia representatives comment on whether
federal funding is in jeopardy for the Navy Shipyard Project, after
Kvaerner Group announced yesterday it was leaving the ship-building
business. (600 words.) By Lisa Fine
</P>
<P>
   PENNSYVLANIA-KOSOVO-REACTION. Pennsylvania lawmakers react to
Kosovo developments. (600 words.) By Lisa Fine
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-LAND-CONSERVATION. There are a number of initiatives on
the table to set aside land for open spaces and wildlife reserves
in Congress. What, if anything, is in there for the wildlife
refuges in the Rio Grande Valley? (Working.) By Robin Brown
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN-THOMPSON-WELFARE. Gov. Tommy Thompson promised
``better Badger babies'' and other next steps in welfare reform at
a conference in Washington Wednesday focusing on the future of
welfare reform. (400 words.) By Elizabeth Hurt
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN-DONORS-KIDS. Four Wisconsin children who have had
successful organ transplants came to Washington Wednesday to thank
members of Congress from the Badger State for supporting organ
donation programs. The children are from Brandon, Elkhorn,
Greenville and Milwaukee. (300 words.) By Elizabeth Hurt
</P>
