   NFL
</P>
<P>
   DRAFT _ Unless contract demands are outrageous, the Cleveland
Browns are expected to take Kentucky's Tim Couch with No. 1 pick in
NFL draft on Saturday. (Pasquarelli, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DRAFT-TRAINERS _ ATLANTA _ Personal trainers like Chip Smith of
Atlanta and Tom Shaw of New Orleans have created a cottage industry
preparing players for the draft. Can they really improve a player's
status? (Pasquarelli, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-SCANDAL _ WASHINGTON _ Congress Wednesday looks at the
International Olympic Committee with a scheduled House Commerce,
Science and Transportation Committee review of the IOC's Salt Lake
City 2002 Winter Olympics bribery scandal. If found wanting during
the hearings, the IOC's tax exempt status could be revoked.
(Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
