   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-USC-HOLTZ _ After two seasons away from coaching, Lou Holtz
has returned to the sidelines hoping to revive a South Carolina
football program that struggled under former coach Brad Scott.
Holtz is one of only 11 coaches with 200 career victories and his
hiring in December gave the South Carolina program instant
credibility. Holtz, who added son Skip to his USC staff, speaks out
on his return to coaching and the USC program as the Gamecocks
prepare for their annual spring game. (Arey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATECH-QB _ Georgia Tech has one of the nation's top
quarterbacks in rising senior Joe Hamilton and Hamilton is the key
for a team that hopes to contend for a national championship in
1999. An injury to Hamilton, however, would be a severe blow for
the Jackets as his backups have limited experience. One of the keys
for the Jackets during spring practice is gaining experience for
the reserve QBs with redshirt freshman Jermaine Crenshaw and
sophomore George Godsey under the microscope. The key to the team's
success could be found in a reserve QB. (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22. WITH PHOTOS (of Crenshaw and Godsey).
</P>
