<P>
   OTHER . . .
</P>
<P>
   HOMETOWN-HEROES _ BELLE, W.Va. _ Across the Kanawha River, the
road signs along Cabin Creek hollow proudly proclaim: ``Home of
Jerry West, NBA great.'' But on this side of the Chelyan Bridge,
where the DuPont chemical plant lights the valley sky even at
midnight, there is nothing to let you know that Belle (population
1,421) and the neighboring community of Rand can claim two big-time
hometown heroes _ Randy Moss and Jason Williams. Not since Bill
Russell and Frank Robinson more than 40 years ago have two
first-year players from the same high school made as big a
major-league splash as Moss and Williams. That Moss and Williams
come from the same small school in Appalachia and have traveled
winding paths more treacherous than a narrow mountain road make
their stories even more intriquing. (Curtright, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 44.
</P>
