<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Meet Joe Black'' (PG-13) _ Director Martin Brest's
ponderous, three-hour update of ``Death Takes a Holiday'' wastes a
good cast, led by Anthony Hopkins. It's more interested in
corporate politics than the romance between Clair Forlani and Brad
Pitt, playing a puppyish Grim Reaper. Priced for VHS rental;
available on DVD for $26.98. Grade: D +
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``One Tough Cop'' (R) _ One tired formula flick. Stephen
Baldwin stars as an NYPD detective torn between duty to his badge
or to a childhood pal (Mike McGlone), who is now a member of a
crime family. This solid cop procedural is fact-based but plays
like a dozen fictional flicks you've seen before. Grade: C
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray
