</P>
<P>
   GAS-PRICES _ (Los Angeles) _ California State Attorney General
Bill Lockyer launches an investigation into possible price gasoline
gouging by oil companies, which could result in legal actions aimed
at reducing soaring gas prices. (Will move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news files.) By Troy Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   BOND-DEFEAT _ (Los Angeles) _ Mayor Richard Riordan and LAPD
Chief Bernard C. Parks blamed San Fernando Valley voters for the
defeat of Proposition 1, which would have raised property taxes to
pay for $744 million in public safety improvements. (Will move in
the ``n'' California news file.) By Rick Orlov, Michael Coit and
Jesse Hiestand.
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-REFORM _ (Los Angeles) _ With the victory of Mayor
Richard Riordan's school board slate, the winners say they intend
to forge better board relations and push for reforms. (Will move in
the ``n'' California news file.) By David Baker and Greg Gittrich.
</P>
<P>
   GOOD-SAMARITAN _ (Los Angeles) _ Ernest LeGault panicked when he
realized he'd driven off to work with his wallet and electronic
organizer on the roof of his Ford Explorer. But he was equally
shocked when the cops called to tell him he had a guardian angel:
landscaper Ismael Gutierrez, who found the oversized wallet three
blocks from LeGault's Encino home and promptly turned it in at the
LAPD's West Valley station. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.) By Jesse Hiestand.
</P>
