A8353 &Cx1f; tab-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-KIDS:FACES:'NSYNC'S-C     04-14 0306
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:FACES:'N </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FACES: 'N CONVERSATION WITH 'N SYNC'S CHRIS 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
 SYNC'S-CHRIS-CLASSACTS-NYTSF  World rights. 
 By ANGELICA LARA 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Is there a girl out there who doesn't know about 'N Sync?
</P>
<P>
   Unless you've been hiding in a cave, you probably are fully
aware. With all the buzz, CLASS ACTS managed to steal a few minutes
with 27-year-old 'N Sync member Chris.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How are things going with you guys?
</P>
<P>
   A: We're on tour right now. We've put a lot of sleepless nights
into it. It's always fun.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I know there are tons of 'N Sync fans, but how do you respond
to all the negative energy out there?
</P>
<P>
   A: We try not to read our press. I mean, even if it's good or
bad, we don't read it. We put it behind us. We play for our fans.
It's all just opinions.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Do you ever get tired of the mobs of fans?
</P>
<P>
   A: Not really. It's always nice to be recognized. We try to make
time for our fans.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Is there anything that you think could break y'all up?
</P>
<P>
   A: I don't think so. We try not to let things come between us.
If we have a disagreement, we always quash it before the show.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How does your family feel about yr success?
</P>
<P>
   A: They're very supportive. They're just happy that I'm happy.
They would be supportive of anything I chose to do, as long as I
was happy.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Do you each take on certain roles in the group?
</P>
<P>
   A: No, we're not the Spice Girls. There isn't like a sporty one
and whatever. We all have our own personalities, and some mix and
some are different.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
