<HEADLINE>
STAR STRUCK? CHECK OUT YOUR WEEK 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By Students SARABETH BALON and NICK FOREMAN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before finalizing your activities, take time to read the
following horoscope, which is a fun way to plan your week.
</P>
<P>
   ARIES (March 21 - April): A family argument will arise in your
household. Your best bet will be to not take sides. The scene may
become ugly if no one will compromise. It is your job to be the
mediator of this situation. You have been in a similar disagreement
with a friend; you will know precisely what to do.
</P>
<P>
   TAURUS (April 20 - May 20): You will receive good news
concerning your summer plans in the next few days. Do not forget to
say `thank you' to the necessary people. Your gratitude will be
very much appreciated. You will also encounter a new friend this
week. Do not try to push them away because they are part of your
usual group of friends.
</P>
<P>
   GEMINI (May 21 - June 20): April and May are the most hectic
months of your year. To make sure that you are able to stay on top
of the situation, you need to eat from the correct food groups. You
must also get a regimented amount of sleep. If you do not take care
of yourour health may wear thin.
</P>
<P>
   CANCER (June 21 - July 22): You need to do something you have
been putting off for the longest time. You realize over and over
again that procrastination is your biggest problem. Do something
about it. If you try to get on top of things, your problems will
begin to diminish gre that is hard to find these days. Keep up the
good work, and try to involve your friends more in what you do. It
is amazing what you can complete when you all have the same goal.
</P>
<P>
   CAPRICORN (Dec. 22 - Jan. 19): You will be faced with a very
difficult decision really soon. However, there is good news. Before
then, you will have many smallerto make to help you prepare. They
will not be insignificantly small, so you need to take them
seriously. Play your cards right, and this weekend will open wide
for you and a cutie.
</P>
<P>
   AQUARIUS (Jan. 20 - Feb. 18): You cannot let a secret eat away
at you. You have to get it off your chest and out in the open if it
starts to bug you or keep you awake at n in trust, but if you do
tell and it is for the better, there is no way that people can be
mad at you. You are a great friend, and friends will see your point
of view before too long.
</P>
<P>
   PISCES (Feb. 19 - March 20): Give a little time to yourself this
week. It has been a long time since you have sat and thought about
what all is going on. You need to develop your own opinion before
you can listen to other people talk on some subjects that you are
facing. The more time you spend by yourself, the more you are
happier with who you are.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
