<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are planning for
Page 1, Thursday, April 15, 1999. The N.Y. Times News Service Night
Supervisor is Ned Kilkelly; phone: (888) 346-9867.
</P>
<P>
   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels) _ Serbs say that Nato hit a refugee
convoy Wednesday, killing 75 civilians. NATO says it hit a military
convoy and that Serbs then massacred civilians to make it look as
if NATO had killed them. NATO says it has a videotape that supports
this. By Michael R. Gordon. With map.
</P>
<P>
   A-hed lede with photo of scene.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
