<SLUG> BC-TV-ROSS-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHEREVER YOU ARE, DR. ROSS, I WILL FIND YOU 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By JOHN LEVESQUE  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   What a cad! Almost two months and not a peep out of Doug Ross,
the peevish pediatrician from ``ER.'' Two months! Where are his
manners?
</P>
<P>
   Oh, right. He doesn't have any.
</P>
<P>
   Still, you may recall that I wrote him in February, right after
he walked out on all his friends at County General in Chicago and
hinted that he might be heading for Portland, Ore., or Seattle. Has
he written back? Nope. Has he shown his face? Uh-uh. Bubkes. No
letter. No e-mail. Not even a phone call, and all he has to do is
dial 10-10 CHEAPSKATE. James Garner said so. Or Dennis Miller?
Whatever.
</P>
<P>
   Nothing else to do but try again.
</P>
<P>
   Dear Dr. Ross,
</P>
<P>
   Word is you've been in Communicado, which I understand is very
pleasant this time of year as long as the sand fleas haven't
hatched. But is there no post office in Communicado? No telephone
booth? No fax machine next to the nacho-cheese pump at the
quickee-mart?
</P>
<P>
   Rest assured that your failure to reply to my letter of Feb. 25
has been duly noted by the human relations directors of every
hospital and clinic in the Puget Sound region, including the Mold
Spore Institute and its new offshoot, the Constant Runny Nose
Clinic.
</P>
<P>
   But this isn't about your future in the Magnificent Moist, Doug.
We'll deal with your qualifications as a physician later, and don't
think that lying low for a while will make people here forget what
you did in Chicago: lying high, insubordination, failure to steer
into the skid. These things will stay on your record for a long
time, mister, possibly as long as it takes Peter Benton to smile.
</P>
<P>
   Anyway, recent developments in Chicago have forced me to
redouble efforts to reach you. This letter is about being a man,
Doug. An hombre. A mensch. A chilovyek.
</P>
<P>
   Surprised that I know Russian? Me too. But I thought it might
make you think of Carol Hathaway, your Ukrainian princess, the
woman who adores you, though I can't figure out why.
</P>
<P>
   She's pregnant, Doug. With child! In a family way! Bun in the
oven! And you da man!
</P>
<P>
   What's up with that? You're a doctor, for Pete's sake. And who's
Pete? He shouldn't be your main concern right now. Haven't you ever
heard of pro, pro, protection?
</P>
<P>
   Carol says she hasn't heard from you since you left Chicago, yet
your picture in USA Today shows you at the Playboy Mansion
celebrating Hugh Hefner's birthday last weekend. Says you attended
under the name George Clooney.
</P>
<P>
   Nice try, Doug. But I'll track you down. And when I do, I'll
make you do right by Carol or, or, or I'll start watching ``48
Hours'' on CBS. I will.
</P>
<P>
   Sincerely yours,
</P>
<P>
   John Levesque
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
