</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Panel decries IOC's reform pace
 &HT;    By Ken Foskett
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Members of a Senate panel on Wednesday warned the
International Olympic Committee to institute prompt reforms or face
congressional sanctions.
</P>
<P>
   Several senators called for the resignation of IOC President
Juan Antonio Samaranch because of the Olympic gift-giving scandal.
But former Majority Leader George Mitchell of Maine recommended
