<SLUG> BC-MACDONALD-COM-NYT </SLUG>
  
 NEW PRESIDENT FOR MacDONALD COMMUNICATIONS  
 (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ MacDonald Communications Corp. has named Barbara
Litrell president, succeeding J.C. MacDonald, who remains chief
executive.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Litrell, 55, had been vice president and group publisher at
Working Woman and Working Mother magazines, which are both
published by MacDonald Communications. As president, she will
continue to oversee the business operations of the magazines as
well as the company's other units, which include MC2 Conferences
and the Businesswomen's Research Institute.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
